---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Avela Travel | The Avela Experience in Nosara, Costa Rica"
  description="Avela Travel was built by people who live in Nosara. We know every villa, chef, boat captain, and trail, and we are here to make your trip extraordinary."
  image="/images/zenith/DSC04983-HDR.jpg"
>

  <!-- Page Header -->
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="page-header-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow reveal">Our story</p>
      <h1 class="reveal reveal-delay-1">
        Built by people<br />
        <em>who live here</em>
      </h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="section about-intro">
    <div class="section-inner about-intro-inner">
      <div class="about-intro-img reveal">
        <img
          src="/images/villas/raintree/01-view-sunset-infinity-pool.jpg"
          alt="Sunset view from a luxury villa's second-story infinity pool overlooking the jungle, Nosara, Costa Rica"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
         width="800" height="1000"/>
      </div>
      <div class="about-intro-text reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <p class="eyebrow">Why Nosara</p>
        <h2>A place that changes the way you see time</h2>
        <p>
          Nosara sits inside Nicoya, one of the world's five Blue Zones, the rare places
          where people routinely live past 100, stay active and connected, and maintain
          a relationship with nature that most of the world has forgotten.
        </p>
        <p>
          It is not a resort town. There are no cruise ships, no chain hotels, no all-inclusive
          wristbands. What you find instead is a community of surfers, yogis, farmers, chefs,
          and expats who came for a week and never left. The food is extraordinary. The surf
          is consistent. The jungle is loud in the best way.
        </p>
        <p>
          Avela was built to give every guest access to that experience, fully and without
          the usual friction of trying to figure it out from scratch.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The people behind Avela -->
  <section class="section team" id="team">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="team-header reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Who we are</p>
        <h2>The people behind Avela</h2>
        <p class="team-lede">
          Avela was born from years of curating experiences. Stacie through Weddings Nosara,
          Jordanny through ocean and adventure tours, and a shared belief that Nosara can be
          elevated without compromising what makes it special. We host in English and Spanish,
          work from a heart-centered place, and answer every message ourselves.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="team-grid">
        <article class="team-card reveal">
          <div class="team-photo">
            <img
              src="/images/team/stacie-cofounder-avela-travel-nosara.jpg"
              alt="Stacie, co-founder of Avela Travel and Head of Hospitality, Nosara, Costa Rica"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
              width="600"
              height="800"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="team-body">
            <p class="eyebrow">Co-Founder · Head of Hospitality</p>
            <h3>Stacie</h3>
            <p class="team-bio">
              Fifteen years in corporate travel taught me what high-touch hospitality feels
              like when it's done right. President's clubs, executive retreats, luxury
              offsites. When Weddings Nosara took off and clients kept telling us the same
              thing about the experiences we built around their day, Jordanny and I realized
              we were onto something that needed a name of its own. Avela is the curation I
              wished I'd had: elevated, never at the expense of authenticity, built around
              deep respect for the local providers and unique places that make Nosara what
              it is.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="team-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <div class="team-photo">
            <img
              src="/images/team/jordanny-cofounder-avela-travel-nosara.jpeg"
              alt="Jordanny, co-founder of Avela Travel leading Adventures and Local Knowledge, Nosara, Costa Rica"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
              width="600"
              height="800"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="team-body">
            <p class="eyebrow">Co-Founder · Adventures &amp; Local Knowledge</p>
            <h3>Jordanny</h3>
            <p class="team-bio">
              <em>Personal note from Jordanny coming soon.</em>
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="team-meta reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="team-meta-item">
          <span class="team-meta-num">2025</span>
          <span class="team-meta-label">Founded</span>
        </div>
        <div class="team-meta-item">
          <span class="team-meta-num">EN / ES</span>
          <span class="team-meta-label">Languages</span>
        </div>
        <div class="team-meta-item">
          <span class="team-meta-num">Nosara</span>
          <span class="team-meta-label">On the ground</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Press strip. Borrowed credibility from Stacie's other Nosara business -->
  <section class="section press">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="press-inner reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Track record</p>
        <p class="press-lede">
          Co-founder Stacie also leads <a href="https://www.instagram.com/weddingsnosara" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Weddings Nosara</a>,
          her destination event-planning business, which has been featured in:
        </p>
        <ul class="press-list" role="list">
          <li>Brides</li>
          <li>Martha Stewart Weddings</li>
          <li>100 Layer Cake</li>
          <li>Jet Fete</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our commitment: integrity, impact, legacy -->
  <section class="section commitment">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="commitment-inner reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Integrity · Impact · Legacy</p>
        <h2>Our commitment to Nosara</h2>
        <div class="commitment-body">
          <p>
            Nosara is growing fast. Growth always comes with a choice. We want Avela to be
            part of protecting this place, not part of what dilutes it.
          </p>
          <p>
            We commit to the local providers, the unique locations, and the people who
            make Nosara what it is. We measure success not just by what we earn, but by
            the impact we leave, by being on the right side of change for the place we love.
          </p>
          <p class="commitment-close">
            This is the family legacy we want to leave for our sons, daughters,
            friends, and community.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Values -->
  <section class="section values" style="background: var(--sand);">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="values-header reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">How we work</p>
        <h2>Local knowledge, applied with care</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="values-grid">
        {[
          {
            num: '01',
            title: 'We only recommend what we know',
            body: 'Every villa on our list has been visited by our team. Every chef has cooked for us. We turn down partnerships when the quality is not right.',
          },
          {
            num: '02',
            title: 'Our interests are aligned with yours',
            body: 'We curate your entire trip: villa, chef, activities, transport. Our focus is always on making your experience as good as it can possibly be.',
          },
          {
            num: '03',
            title: 'We are here when things change',
            body: 'Avela Experience clients have a direct line to our team throughout their stay. Conditions shift, plans evolve, and requests come up at all hours. We handle it.',
          },
          {
            num: '04',
            title: 'We keep it honest',
            body: 'If a villa is booked or not right for your group, we will say so. We would rather help you find the perfect fit than push something that does not match.',
          },
        ].map(({ num, title, body }, i) => (
          <div class={`value-card reveal reveal-delay-${i + 1}`}>
            <span class="value-num">{num}</span>
            <h3>{title}</h3>
            <p>{body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Blue Zone -->
  <section class="section blue-zone">
    <div class="section-inner blue-zone-inner">
      <div class="blue-zone-text reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Blue Zone living</p>
        <h2>
          The Nicoya Peninsula is one of five places on earth where people live longest
        </h2>
        <p>
          Researchers studying longevity have identified five Blue Zones around the world.
          The Nicoya Peninsula, where Nosara sits, is one of them. The lifestyle here is
          active by default, social by nature, and grounded in whole food and unhurried time.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our wellness experiences are rooted in this tradition: morning yoga on hilltop
          platforms, sound healing in open-air studios, Blue Zone diet cooking classes,
          and spa treatments that use local plants and techniques.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Plan a Wellness Stay</a>
      </div>
      <div class="blue-zone-img reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <img
          src="/images/nosara/pink-island.jpg"
          alt="Aerial of the pink-sand island spit off the Nosara coast, Costa Rica"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
         width="800" height="1000"/>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Monkey Head Adventures -->
  <section class="section partner" style="background: var(--green-deep);">
    <div class="section-inner partner-inner">
      <div class="partner-text reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Our ocean partner</p>
        <h2>Monkey Head Adventures</h2>
        <p>
          Avela partners exclusively with Monkey Head Adventures for all ocean experiences.
          They own and operate two private boats based out of Nosara, crewed by people who
          have spent their lives on this stretch of the Pacific.
        </p>
        <p>
          Whether you are after world-class sportfishing, a snorkeling trip to the offshore
          rocks, or a sunset cruise with a bottle of local wine, Monkey Head runs it well.
          Their knowledge of conditions, marine life, and the best seasonal windows is second
          to none on the Nicoya coast.
        </p>
        <div class="partner-services">
          {['Sportfishing', 'Snorkeling', 'Sunset cruises', 'Whale watching (seasonal)', 'Dolphin tours'].map((s) => (
            <span class="partner-tag">{s}</span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="partner-img reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <video
          src="/videos/dont-send-help-monkey-head.mp4"
          poster="/videos/dont-send-help-monkey-head-poster.jpg"
          autoplay
          muted
          loop
          playsinline
          preload="metadata"
          aria-label="Monkey Head Adventures boat off the Nosara coast"
        ></video>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Nosara map -->
  <section class="section nosara-map" style="background: var(--cream);">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="nosara-map-header reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Where we are</p>
        <h2>Nosara, <em>Nicoya Peninsula</em></h2>
        <p class="nosara-map-lede">
          A short stretch of coast on Costa Rica's Pacific side. Every Avela trip happens within
          these few kilometers. Beaches, jungle, and airstrip all sit within a fifteen-minute drive
          of each other.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="nosara-map-wrap reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <svg
          class="nosara-map-svg"
          viewBox="0 0 900 600"
          role="img"
          aria-label="Stylized map of Nosara, Costa Rica showing key beaches, the airstrip, and town"
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        >
          <defs>
            <linearGradient id="ocean" x1="0" x2="0" y1="0" y2="1">
              <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#cfe3df"/>
              <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#a9c9c1"/>
            </linearGradient>
            <linearGradient id="land" x1="0" x2="1" y1="0" y2="0">
              <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#e9e0c9"/>
              <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#cbb98a"/>
            </linearGradient>
            <linearGradient id="jungle" x1="0" x2="1" y1="0" y2="0">
              <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#7e8d5d"/>
              <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#566a3e"/>
            </linearGradient>
          </defs>

          <!-- Ocean background -->
          <rect width="900" height="600" fill="url(#ocean)"/>

          <!-- Land mass: stylized coastline -->
          <path
            d="M 240 0
               C 260 60, 230 90, 250 140
               C 270 180, 220 210, 250 250
               C 280 280, 230 310, 260 360
               C 280 400, 240 430, 270 480
               C 290 520, 260 560, 280 600
               L 900 600
               L 900 0 Z"
            fill="url(#land)"
          />
          <!-- Jungle gradient overlay -->
          <path
            d="M 540 0
               L 900 0
               L 900 600
               L 540 600 Z"
            fill="url(#jungle)"
            opacity="0.55"
          />

          <!-- Topographic contour lines over the hills -->
          <g stroke="#3a4f41" stroke-width="0.6" fill="none" opacity="0.22">
            <path d="M 600 120 Q 710 142, 830 120"/>
            <path d="M 625 178 Q 725 202, 845 180"/>
            <path d="M 590 240 Q 705 262, 835 246"/>
            <path d="M 615 318 Q 725 342, 850 325"/>
            <path d="M 600 398 Q 712 420, 842 404"/>
            <path d="M 622 470 Q 725 492, 852 476"/>
          </g>

          <!-- Subtle wave lines in ocean -->
          <g stroke="#8aafa6" stroke-width="0.7" fill="none" opacity="0.4">
            <path d="M 30 90 Q 90 80, 150 90 T 230 95"/>
            <path d="M 40 180 Q 100 170, 160 180 T 230 185"/>
            <path d="M 30 280 Q 90 270, 150 280 T 240 285"/>
            <path d="M 40 380 Q 100 370, 160 380 T 250 385"/>
            <path d="M 30 480 Q 90 470, 150 480 T 270 488"/>
          </g>

          <!-- Río Nosara, flowing from the hills to the boca -->
          <path
            d="M 815 205 C 690 232, 600 250, 510 268 C 420 286, 335 290, 252 297"
            stroke="#8fb3c9" stroke-width="3" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.85"
          />
          <text x="372" y="282" font-family="Playfair Display, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="11" fill="#5d83a0" opacity="0.9">Río Nosara</text>

          <!-- Road network (dashed) -->
          <g stroke="#b8742a" stroke-width="1.4" fill="none" stroke-dasharray="2 5" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.5">
            <path d="M 430 270 L 262 378"/>
            <path d="M 430 270 C 360 238, 300 214, 246 196"/>
            <path d="M 246 196 C 232 140, 240 95, 248 58"/>
            <path d="M 260 384 C 262 440, 266 492, 275 528"/>
            <path d="M 430 270 C 540 300, 640 360, 720 470"/>
          </g>

          <!-- Beach markers + labels (left side along coast) -->
          <!-- Ostional -->
          <circle cx="248" cy="55" r="6" fill="#3a4f41"/>
          <line x1="254" y1="55" x2="320" y2="55" stroke="#3a4f41" stroke-width="1"/>
          <text x="328" y="50" font-family="DM Sans, sans-serif" font-size="13" font-weight="500" letter-spacing="2" fill="#3a4f41">OSTIONAL</text>
          <text x="328" y="66" font-family="Playfair Display, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="12" fill="#3a4f41" opacity="0.7">Turtle arribada</text>

          <!-- Playa Pelada -->
          <circle cx="245" cy="195" r="6" fill="#3a4f41"/>
          <line x1="251" y1="195" x2="320" y2="195" stroke="#3a4f41" stroke-width="1"/>
          <text x="328" y="190" font-family="DM Sans, sans-serif" font-size="13" font-weight="500" letter-spacing="2" fill="#3a4f41">PLAYA PELADA</text>
          <text x="328" y="206" font-family="Playfair Display, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="12" fill="#3a4f41" opacity="0.7">Tidepools, sunsets</text>

          <!-- Nosara town + airstrip -->
          <circle cx="430" cy="270" r="6" fill="#b8742a"/>
          <line x1="436" y1="270" x2="520" y2="270" stroke="#b8742a" stroke-width="1"/>
          <text x="528" y="265" font-family="DM Sans, sans-serif" font-size="13" font-weight="500" letter-spacing="2" fill="#b8742a">NOSARA TOWN</text>
          <text x="528" y="281" font-family="Playfair Display, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="12" fill="#3a4f41" opacity="0.75">Airstrip + village</text>

          <!-- River mouth (boca) -->
          <circle cx="252" cy="297" r="4" fill="#5d83a0" opacity="0.85"/>
          <text x="259" y="301" font-family="Playfair Display, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="11" fill="#5d83a0" opacity="0.8">La Boca · river mouth</text>

          <!-- Playa Guiones -->
          <circle cx="258" cy="380" r="8" fill="#b8742a"/>
          <line x1="266" y1="380" x2="340" y2="380" stroke="#b8742a" stroke-width="1.2"/>
          <text x="348" y="375" font-family="DM Sans, sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="500" letter-spacing="2" fill="#b8742a">PLAYA GUIONES</text>
          <text x="348" y="393" font-family="Playfair Display, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="12" fill="#3a4f41" opacity="0.75">Sand-bottom point break · the surf</text>

          <!-- Punta Guiones -->
          <circle cx="256" cy="436" r="4" fill="#3a4f41" opacity="0.8"/>
          <text x="264" y="440" font-family="Playfair Display, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="11" fill="#3a4f41" opacity="0.7">Punta Guiones</text>

          <!-- Las Huacas hills marker -->
          <text x="640" y="320" font-family="Playfair Display, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="14" fill="#fbf8f2" opacity="0.85" text-anchor="middle">LAS HUACAS HILLS</text>
          <text x="640" y="338" font-family="Playfair Display, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="12" fill="#fbf8f2" opacity="0.6" text-anchor="middle">Ocean-view villas</text>

          <!-- Playa Garza (south) -->
          <circle cx="275" cy="530" r="6" fill="#3a4f41"/>
          <line x1="281" y1="530" x2="360" y2="530" stroke="#3a4f41" stroke-width="1"/>
          <text x="368" y="525" font-family="DM Sans, sans-serif" font-size="13" font-weight="500" letter-spacing="2" fill="#3a4f41">PLAYA GARZA</text>
          <text x="368" y="541" font-family="Playfair Display, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="12" fill="#3a4f41" opacity="0.7">Monkey Head harbor</text>

          <!-- N indicator -->
          <g transform="translate(70, 60)">
            <circle r="22" fill="#fbf8f2" stroke="#3a4f41" stroke-width="1"/>
            <text y="6" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Playfair Display, serif" font-size="18" font-weight="600" fill="#3a4f41">N</text>
          </g>

          <!-- Compass arrow -->
          <line x1="70" y1="40" x2="70" y2="20" stroke="#3a4f41" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <polygon points="70,16 67,22 73,22" fill="#3a4f41"/>

          <!-- Pacific Ocean label -->
          <text x="120" y="320" font-family="Playfair Display, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="18" fill="#3a4f41" opacity="0.5">Pacific Ocean</text>

          <!-- Approximate scale bar -->
          <g transform="translate(110, 565)">
            <line x1="0" y1="0" x2="110" y2="0" stroke="#3a4f41" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.7"/>
            <line x1="0" y1="-4" x2="0" y2="4" stroke="#3a4f41" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.7"/>
            <line x1="110" y1="-4" x2="110" y2="4" stroke="#3a4f41" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.7"/>
            <text x="55" y="-8" text-anchor="middle" font-family="DM Sans, sans-serif" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1" fill="#3a4f41" opacity="0.65">~ 2 km</text>
          </g>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <div class="nosara-map-legend reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="legend-item">
          <span class="legend-dot legend-dot-primary"></span>
          <span>Where the surf, the town, and the airstrip are</span>
        </div>
        <div class="legend-item">
          <span class="legend-dot legend-dot-secondary"></span>
          <span>Day-trip beaches and excursion sites</span>
        </div>
        <a
          class="nosara-map-link"
          href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Nosara,+Provincia+de+Guanacaste,+Costa+Rica"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          View Nosara on Google Maps →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section about-cta" style="background: var(--dark);">
    <div class="section-inner about-cta-inner reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Start the conversation</p>
      <h2>Tell us about your trip</h2>
      <p>
        We keep our planning calls short and our questions specific. Share your dates, group
        size, and what matters most. We will take care of the rest.
      </p>
      <div class="about-cta-actions">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Plan My Trip</a>
        <a href="/villas" class="btn-ghost">Browse Villas</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Page Header */
  .page-header {
    background: var(--dark);
    padding: 160px var(--gutter) clamp(60px, 8vw, 100px);
  }

  .page-header-inner {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-header .eyebrow {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    color: var(--warm-cream);
    line-height: 1.05;
  }

  .page-header h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--amber);
  }

  /* Intro */
  .about-intro-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 7rem);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .about-intro-img {
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .about-intro-img img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .about-intro-text .eyebrow {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .about-intro-text h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.6rem);
    color: var(--green-deep);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .about-intro-text p {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: rgba(19, 18, 16, 0.65);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  /* The people behind Avela */
  .team {
    background: var(--cream);
  }
  .team-header {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto 3.5rem;
  }
  .team-header h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    color: var(--green-deep);
    margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .team-lede {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(19, 18, 16, 0.65);
  }
  .team-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 780px) {
    .team-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3.5rem; }
  }
  .team-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .team-body {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 360px;
  }
  .team-photo {
    aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--dark);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 340px;
  }
  .team-photo img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    transition: transform 0.8s var(--ease-smooth);
  }
  .team-card:hover .team-photo img {
    transform: scale(1.03);
  }
  .team-body .eyebrow {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .team-body h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
